285 VOID
286 MiDetermineNode (
287  IN PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex,
288  IN PMMPFN Pfn
289  )
290 
291 /*++
292 
293 Routine Description:
294 
295  This routine is called during initial freelist population or when
296  physical memory is being hot-added. It then determines which node
297  (in a multinode NUMA system) the physical memory resides in, and
298  marks the PFN entry accordingly.
299 
300  N.B. The actual page to node determination is machine dependent
301  and done by a routine in the chipset driver or the HAL, called
302  via the MmPageToNode function pointer.
303 
304 Arguments:
305 
306  PageFrameIndex - Supplies the physical page number.
307 
308  Pfn - Supplies a pointer to the PFN database element.
309 
310 Return Value:
311 
312  None.
313 
314 Environment:
315 
316  None although typically this routine is called with the PFN
317  database locked.
318 
319 --*/
320 
321 {
322  ULONG Temp;
323 
324  ASSERT (Pfn == MI_PFN_ELEMENT(PageFrameIndex));
325 
326  Temp = MmPageToNode (PageFrameIndex);
327 
328  ASSERT (Temp < MAXIMUM_CCNUMA_NODES);
329 
330  Pfn->u3.e1.PageColor = (USHORT) Temp;
331 }

336 BOOLEAN
337 MmInitSystem (
338  IN ULONG Phase,
339  IN PLOADER_PARAMETER_BLOCK LoaderBlock
340  )
341 
342 /*++
343 
344 Routine Description:
345 
346  This function is called during Phase 0, phase 1 and at the end
347  of phase 1 ("phase 2") initialization.
348 
349  Phase 0 initializes the memory management paging functions,
350  nonpaged and paged pool, the PFN database, etc.
351 
352  Phase 1 initializes the section objects, the physical memory
353  object, and starts the memory management system threads.
354 
355  Phase 2 frees memory used by the OsLoader.
356 
357 Arguments:
358 
359  Phase - System initialization phase.
360 
361  LoaderBlock - Supplies a pointer to the system loader block.
362 
363 Return Value:
364 
365  Returns TRUE if the initialization was successful.
366 
367 Environment:
368 
369  Kernel Mode Only. System initialization.
370 
371 --*/
372 
373 {
374  ULONG Color;
375  PSLIST_ENTRY SingleListEntry;
376  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
377  HANDLE ThreadHandle;
378  OBJECT_ATTRIBUTES ObjectAttributes;
379  PMMPTE PointerPte;
380  PMMPTE PointerPde;
381  PMMPTE StartPde;
382  PMMPTE EndPde;
383  PMMPFN Pfn1;
384  PFN_NUMBER i, j;
385  PFN_NUMBER DeferredMdlEntries;
386  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
387  PFN_NUMBER DirectoryFrameIndex;
388  MMPTE TempPte;
389  KIRQL OldIrql;
390  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
391  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry;
392  ULONG_PTR MaximumSystemCacheSize;
393  PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS NtHeaders;
394  ULONG_PTR SystemPteMultiplier;
395  ULONG_PTR DefaultSystemViewSize;
396  ULONG_PTR SessionEnd;
397  SIZE_T SystemViewMax;
398  SIZE_T HydraImageMax;
399  SIZE_T HydraViewMax;
400  SIZE_T HydraPoolMax;
401  SIZE_T HydraSpaceUsedForSystemViews;
402  BOOLEAN IncludeType[LoaderMaximum];
403  LOGICAL AutosizingFragment;
404  PULONG Bitmap;
405  PPHYSICAL_MEMORY_RUN Run;
406  ULONG VerifierFlags;
407 #if DBG
408  MMPTE Pointer;
409 #endif
410 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
411  LOGICAL FirstPpe;
412  PMMPTE StartPpe;
413 #endif
414 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
415  LOGICAL FirstPxe;
416  PMMPTE StartPxe;
417 #endif
418 #if defined(_X86_)
419  PCHAR ReducedUserVaOption;
420  ULONG UserVaLimit;
421  ULONG ReductionInBytes;
422  ULONG ReductionInPages;
423  LOGICAL ReduceSystemCacheForPtes;
424 #endif
425 
426  j = 0;
427  PointerPde = NULL;
428 
429  //
430  // Make sure structure alignment is okay.
431  //
432 
433  if (Phase == 0) {
434  MmThrottleTop = 450;
435  MmThrottleBottom = 127;
436 
437  //
438  // Point various event thresholds at a temp unsignaled event
439  // since real event creation is not available until phase 1.
440  //
441 
442  KeInitializeEvent (&MiTempEvent, NotificationEvent, FALSE);
443 
444  MiLowMemoryEvent = &MiTempEvent;
445  MiHighMemoryEvent = &MiTempEvent;
446 
447  MiLowPagedPoolEvent = &MiTempEvent;
448  MiHighPagedPoolEvent = &MiTempEvent;
449 
450  MiLowNonPagedPoolEvent = &MiTempEvent;
451  MiHighNonPagedPoolEvent = &MiTempEvent;
452 
453  //
454  // Set the highest user address, the system range start address, the
455  // user probe address, and the virtual bias.
456  //
457 
458 #if defined(_WIN64)
459 
460  MmHighestUserAddress = MI_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS;
461  MmUserProbeAddress = MI_USER_PROBE_ADDRESS;
462  MmSystemRangeStart = MI_SYSTEM_RANGE_START;
463 
464 #else
465 
466  MmHighestUserAddress = (PVOID)(KSEG0_BASE - 0x10000 - 1);
467  MmUserProbeAddress = KSEG0_BASE - 0x10000;
468  MmSystemRangeStart = (PVOID)KSEG0_BASE;
469 
470 #endif
471 
472  MiHighestUserPte = MiGetPteAddress (MmHighestUserAddress);
473  MiHighestUserPde = MiGetPdeAddress (MmHighestUserAddress);
474 
475 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
476  MiHighestUserPpe = MiGetPpeAddress (MmHighestUserAddress);
477  MiHighestUserPxe = MiGetPxeAddress (MmHighestUserAddress);
478 #endif
479 
480 #if defined(_X86_) || defined(_AMD64_)
481 
482  MmBootImageSize = LoaderBlock->Extension->LoaderPagesSpanned;
483  MmBootImageSize *= PAGE_SIZE;
484 
485  MmBootImageSize = MI_ROUND_TO_SIZE (MmBootImageSize,
486  MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PDE);
487 
488  ASSERT ((MmBootImageSize % MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PDE) == 0);
489 #endif
490 
491 #if defined(_X86_)
492  MmVirtualBias = LoaderBlock->u.I386.VirtualBias;
493 #endif
494 
495  //
496  // Initialize system and Hydra mapped view sizes.
497  //
498 
499  DefaultSystemViewSize = MM_SYSTEM_VIEW_SIZE;
500  MmSessionSize = MI_SESSION_SPACE_DEFAULT_TOTAL_SIZE;
501  SessionEnd = (ULONG_PTR) MM_SESSION_SPACE_DEFAULT_END;
502 
503 #define MM_MB_MAPPED_BY_PDE (MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PDE / (1024*1024))
504 
505  //
506  // A PDE of virtual space is the minimum system view size allowed.
507  //
508 
509  if (MmSystemViewSize < (MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PDE / (1024*1024))) {
510  MmSystemViewSize = DefaultSystemViewSize;
511  }
512  else {
513 
514  //
515  // The view size has been specified (in megabytes) by the registry.
516  // Validate it.
517  //
518 
519  if (MmVirtualBias == 0) {
520 
521  //
522  // Round the system view size (in megabytes) to a PDE multiple.
523  //
524 
525  MmSystemViewSize = MI_ROUND_TO_SIZE (MmSystemViewSize,
526  MM_MB_MAPPED_BY_PDE);
527 
528  //
529  // NT64 locates system views just after systemwide paged pool,
530  // so the size of the system views are not limited by session
531  // space. Arbitrarily make the maximum a PPE's worth.
532  //
533  //
534  // NT32 shares system view VA space with session VA space due
535  // to the shortage of virtual addresses. Thus increasing the
536  // system view size means potentially decreasing the maximum
537  // session space size.
538  //
539 
540  SystemViewMax = (MI_SESSION_SPACE_MAXIMUM_TOTAL_SIZE) / (1024*1024);
541 
542 #if !defined(_WIN64)
543 
544  //
545  // Ensure at least enough space is left for
546  // the standard default session layout.
547  //
548 
549  SystemViewMax -= (MmSessionSize / (1024*1024));
550 #endif
551 
552  //
553  // Note a view size of -1 will be rounded to zero. Treat -1
554  // as requesting the maximum.
555  //
556 
557  if ((MmSystemViewSize > SystemViewMax) ||
558  (MmSystemViewSize == 0)) {
559 
560  MmSystemViewSize = SystemViewMax;
561  }
562 
563  MmSystemViewSize *= (1024*1024);
564  }
565  else {
566  MmSystemViewSize = DefaultSystemViewSize;
567  }
568  }
569 
570 #if defined(_WIN64)
571  HydraSpaceUsedForSystemViews = 0;
572 #else
573  HydraSpaceUsedForSystemViews = MmSystemViewSize;
574 #endif
575  MiSessionImageEnd = SessionEnd;
576 
577  //
578  // Select reasonable Hydra image, pool and view virtual sizes.
579  // A PDE of virtual space is the minimum size allowed for each type.
580  //
581 
582  if (MmVirtualBias == 0) {
583 
584  if (MmSessionImageSize < MM_MB_MAPPED_BY_PDE) {
585  MmSessionImageSize = MI_SESSION_DEFAULT_IMAGE_SIZE;
586  }
587  else {
588 
589  //
590  // The Hydra image size has been specified (in megabytes)
591  // by the registry.
592  //
593  // Round it to a PDE multiple and validate it.
594  //
595 
596  MmSessionImageSize = MI_ROUND_TO_SIZE (MmSessionImageSize,
597  MM_MB_MAPPED_BY_PDE);
598 
599  HydraImageMax = (MI_SESSION_SPACE_MAXIMUM_TOTAL_SIZE - HydraSpaceUsedForSystemViews - (MmSessionSize - MI_SESSION_DEFAULT_IMAGE_SIZE)) / (1024*1024);
600 
601  //
602  // Note a view size of -1 will be rounded to zero.
603  // Treat -1 as requesting the maximum.
604  //
605 
606  if ((MmSessionImageSize > HydraImageMax) ||
607  (MmSessionImageSize == 0)) {
608  MmSessionImageSize = HydraImageMax;
609  }
610 
611  MmSessionImageSize *= (1024*1024);
612  MmSessionSize -= MI_SESSION_DEFAULT_IMAGE_SIZE;
613  MmSessionSize += MmSessionImageSize;
614  }
615 
616  MiSessionImageStart = SessionEnd - MmSessionImageSize;
617 
618  //
619  // The session image start and size has been established.
620  //
621  // Now initialize the session pool and view ranges which lie
622  // virtually below it.
623  //
624 
625  if (MmSessionViewSize < MM_MB_MAPPED_BY_PDE) {
626  MmSessionViewSize = MI_SESSION_DEFAULT_VIEW_SIZE;
627  }
628  else {
629 
630  //
631  // The Hydra view size has been specified (in megabytes)
632  // by the registry. Validate it.
633  //
634  // Round the Hydra view size to a PDE multiple.
635  //
636 
637  MmSessionViewSize = MI_ROUND_TO_SIZE (MmSessionViewSize,
638  MM_MB_MAPPED_BY_PDE);
639 
640  HydraViewMax = (MI_SESSION_SPACE_MAXIMUM_TOTAL_SIZE - HydraSpaceUsedForSystemViews - (MmSessionSize - MI_SESSION_DEFAULT_VIEW_SIZE)) / (1024*1024);
641 
642  //
643  // Note a view size of -1 will be rounded to zero.
644  // Treat -1 as requesting the maximum.
645  //
646 
647  if ((MmSessionViewSize > HydraViewMax) ||
648  (MmSessionViewSize == 0)) {
649  MmSessionViewSize = HydraViewMax;
650  }
651 
652  MmSessionViewSize *= (1024*1024);
653  MmSessionSize -= MI_SESSION_DEFAULT_VIEW_SIZE;
654  MmSessionSize += MmSessionViewSize;
655  }
656 
657  MiSessionViewStart = SessionEnd - MmSessionImageSize - MI_SESSION_SPACE_WS_SIZE - MI_SESSION_SPACE_STRUCT_SIZE - MmSessionViewSize;
658 
659  //
660  // The session view start and size has been established.
661  //
662  // Now initialize the session pool start and size which lies
663  // virtually just below it.
664  //
665 
666  MiSessionPoolEnd = MiSessionViewStart;
667 
668  if (MmSessionPoolSize < MM_MB_MAPPED_BY_PDE) {
669 
670 #if !defined(_WIN64)
671 
672  //
673  // Professional and below use systemwide paged pool for session
674  // allocations (this decision is made in win32k.sys). Server
675  // and above use real session pool and 16mb isn't enough to
676  // play high end game applications, etc. Since we're not
677  // booted /3GB, try for an additional 16mb now.
678  //
679 
680  if ((MmSessionPoolSize == 0) && (MmProductType != 0x00690057)) {
681 
682  HydraPoolMax = MI_SESSION_SPACE_MAXIMUM_TOTAL_SIZE - HydraSpaceUsedForSystemViews - MmSessionSize;
683  if (HydraPoolMax >= 2 * MI_SESSION_DEFAULT_POOL_SIZE) {
684  MmSessionPoolSize = 2 * MI_SESSION_DEFAULT_POOL_SIZE;
685  MmSessionSize -= MI_SESSION_DEFAULT_POOL_SIZE;
686  MmSessionSize += MmSessionPoolSize;
687  }
688  else {
689  MmSessionPoolSize = MI_SESSION_DEFAULT_POOL_SIZE;
690  }
691  }
692  else
693 #endif
694  MmSessionPoolSize = MI_SESSION_DEFAULT_POOL_SIZE;
695  }
696  else {
697 
698  //
699  // The Hydra pool size has been specified (in megabytes)
700  // by the registry. Validate it.
701  //
702  // Round the Hydra pool size to a PDE multiple.
703  //
704 
705  MmSessionPoolSize = MI_ROUND_TO_SIZE (MmSessionPoolSize,
706  MM_MB_MAPPED_BY_PDE);
707 
708  HydraPoolMax = (MI_SESSION_SPACE_MAXIMUM_TOTAL_SIZE - HydraSpaceUsedForSystemViews - (MmSessionSize - MI_SESSION_DEFAULT_POOL_SIZE)) / (1024*1024);
709 
710  //
711  // Note a view size of -1 will be rounded to zero.
712  // Treat -1 as requesting the maximum.
713  //
714 
715  if ((MmSessionPoolSize > HydraPoolMax) ||
716  (MmSessionPoolSize == 0)) {
717  MmSessionPoolSize = HydraPoolMax;
718  }
719 
720  MmSessionPoolSize *= (1024*1024);
721  MmSessionSize -= MI_SESSION_DEFAULT_POOL_SIZE;
722  MmSessionSize += MmSessionPoolSize;
723  }
724 
725  MiSessionPoolStart = MiSessionPoolEnd - MmSessionPoolSize;
726 
727  MmSessionBase = (ULONG_PTR) MiSessionPoolStart;
728 
729 #if defined (_WIN64)
730 
731  //
732  // Session special pool immediately follows session regular pool
733  // assuming the user has enabled either the verifier or special
734  // pool.
735  //
736 
737  if ((MmVerifyDriverBufferLength != (ULONG)-1) ||
738  ((MmSpecialPoolTag != 0) && (MmSpecialPoolTag != (ULONG)-1))) {
739 
740  MmSessionSize = MI_SESSION_SPACE_MAXIMUM_TOTAL_SIZE;
741  MmSessionSpecialPoolEnd = (PVOID) MiSessionPoolStart;
742  MmSessionBase = MM_SESSION_SPACE_DEFAULT;
743  MmSessionSpecialPoolStart = (PVOID) MmSessionBase;
744  }
745 #endif
746 
747  ASSERT (MmSessionBase + MmSessionSize == SessionEnd);
748  MiSessionSpaceEnd = SessionEnd;
749  MiSessionSpacePageTables = (ULONG)(MmSessionSize / MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PDE);
750 #if !defined (_WIN64)
751  MiSystemViewStart = MmSessionBase - MmSystemViewSize;
752 #endif
753 
754  }
755  else {
756 
757  //
758  // When booted /3GB, no size overrides are allowed due to the
759  // already severely limited virtual address space.
760  // Initialize the other Hydra variables after the system cache.
761  //
762 
763  MmSessionViewSize = MI_SESSION_DEFAULT_VIEW_SIZE;
764  MmSessionPoolSize = MI_SESSION_DEFAULT_POOL_SIZE;
765  MmSessionImageSize = MI_SESSION_DEFAULT_IMAGE_SIZE;
766 
767  MiSessionImageStart = MiSessionImageEnd - MmSessionImageSize;
768 
769 #if defined(_X86PAE_)
770  MmSystemCacheStart = (PVOID) ((ULONG_PTR) MmSystemCacheStart +
771  MM_SYSTEM_CACHE_WORKING_SET_3GB_DELTA);
772 #endif
773  }
774 
775  //
776  // Set the highest section base address.
777  //
778  // N.B. In 32-bit systems this address must be 2gb or less even for
779  // systems that run with 3gb enabled. Otherwise, it would not
780  // be possible to map based sections identically in all processes.
781  //
782 
783  MmHighSectionBase = ((PCHAR)MmHighestUserAddress - 0x800000);
784

1307  // machines anyway, just turn it off in these cases.

1309  // 2. For 64-bit machines, there is plenty of VA space above the

1314  // this case as it doesn't provide any sign extension help and
1315  // therefore we don't allow it to burn up any valuable VA space

2579 PPHYSICAL_MEMORY_DESCRIPTOR
2580 MmInitializeMemoryLimits (
2581  IN PLOADER_PARAMETER_BLOCK LoaderBlock,
2582  IN PBOOLEAN IncludeType,
2583  IN OUT PPHYSICAL_MEMORY_DESCRIPTOR InputMemory OPTIONAL
2584  )
2585 
2586 /*++
2587 
2588 Routine Description:
2589 
2590  This function walks through the loader block's memory
2591  descriptor list and builds a list of contiguous physical
2592  memory blocks of the desired types.
2593 
2594 Arguments:
2595 
2596  LoaderBlock - Supplies a pointer the system loader block.
2597 
2598  IncludeType - Array of BOOLEANS of size LoaderMaximum.
2599  TRUE means include this type of memory in return.
2600 
2601  Memory - If non-NULL, supplies the physical memory blocks to place the
2602  search results in. If NULL, pool is allocated to hold the
2603  returned search results in - the caller must free this pool.
2604 
2605 Return Value:
2606 
2607  A pointer to the physical memory blocks for the requested search or NULL
2608  on failure.
2609 
2610 Environment:
2611 
2612  Kernel Mode Only. System initialization.
2613 
2614 --*/
2615 {
2616  PLIST_ENTRY NextMd;
2617  ULONG i;
2618  ULONG InitialAllocation;
2619  PFN_NUMBER NextPage;
2620  PFN_NUMBER TotalPages;
2621  PPHYSICAL_MEMORY_DESCRIPTOR Memory;
2622  PPHYSICAL_MEMORY_DESCRIPTOR Memory2;
2623  PMEMORY_ALLOCATION_DESCRIPTOR MemoryDescriptor;
2624 
2625  InitialAllocation = 0;
2626 
2627  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT (InputMemory)) {
2628  Memory = InputMemory;
2629  }
2630  else {
2631 
2632  //
2633  // The caller wants us to allocate the return result buffer. Size it
2634  // by allocating the maximum possibly needed as this should not be
2635  // very big (relatively). It is the caller's responsibility to free
2636  // this. Obviously this option can only be requested after pool has
2637  // been initialized.
2638  //
2639 
2640  NextMd = LoaderBlock->MemoryDescriptorListHead.Flink;
2641 
2642  while (NextMd != &LoaderBlock->MemoryDescriptorListHead) {
2643  InitialAllocation += 1;
2644  MemoryDescriptor = CONTAINING_RECORD(NextMd,
2645  MEMORY_ALLOCATION_DESCRIPTOR,
2646  ListEntry);
2647  NextMd = MemoryDescriptor->ListEntry.Flink;
2648  }
2649 
2650  Memory = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
2651  sizeof(PHYSICAL_MEMORY_DESCRIPTOR) + sizeof(PHYSICAL_MEMORY_RUN) * (InitialAllocation - 1),
2652  'lMmM');
2653 
2654  if (Memory == NULL) {
2655  return NULL;
2656  }
2657 
2658  Memory->NumberOfRuns = InitialAllocation;
2659  }
2660 
2661  //
2662  // Walk through the memory descriptors and build the physical memory list.
2663  //
2664 
2665  i = 0;
2666  TotalPages = 0;
2667  NextPage = (PFN_NUMBER) -1;
2668 
2669  NextMd = LoaderBlock->MemoryDescriptorListHead.Flink;
2670 
2671  while (NextMd != &LoaderBlock->MemoryDescriptorListHead) {
2672 
2673  MemoryDescriptor = CONTAINING_RECORD(NextMd,
2674  MEMORY_ALLOCATION_DESCRIPTOR,
2675  ListEntry);
2676 
2677  if (MemoryDescriptor->MemoryType < LoaderMaximum &&
2678  IncludeType [MemoryDescriptor->MemoryType]) {
2679 
2680  TotalPages += MemoryDescriptor->PageCount;
2681 
2682  //
2683  // Merge runs whenever possible.
2684  //
2685 
2686  if (MemoryDescriptor->BasePage == NextPage) {
2687  ASSERT (MemoryDescriptor->PageCount != 0);
2688  Memory->Run[i - 1].PageCount += MemoryDescriptor->PageCount;
2689  NextPage += MemoryDescriptor->PageCount;
2690  }
2691  else {
2692  Memory->Run[i].BasePage = MemoryDescriptor->BasePage;
2693  Memory->Run[i].PageCount = MemoryDescriptor->PageCount;
2694  NextPage = Memory->Run[i].BasePage + Memory->Run[i].PageCount;
2695  i += 1;
2696  }
2697  }
2698  NextMd = MemoryDescriptor->ListEntry.Flink;
2699  }
2700 
2701  ASSERT (i <= Memory->NumberOfRuns);
2702 
2703  if (i == 0) {
2704 
2705  //
2706  // Don't bother shrinking this as the caller will be freeing it
2707  // shortly as it is just an empty list.
2708  //
2709 
2710  Memory->Run[i].BasePage = 0;
2711  Memory->Run[i].PageCount = 0;
2712  }
2713  else if (!ARGUMENT_PRESENT (InputMemory)) {
2714 
2715  //
2716  // Shrink the buffer (if possible) now that the final size is known.
2717  //
2718 
2719  if (InitialAllocation > i) {
2720  Memory2 = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
2721  sizeof(PHYSICAL_MEMORY_DESCRIPTOR) + sizeof(PHYSICAL_MEMORY_RUN) * (i - 1),
2722  'lMmM');
2723 
2724  if (Memory2 != NULL) {
2725  RtlCopyMemory (Memory2->Run,
2726  Memory->Run,
2727  sizeof(PHYSICAL_MEMORY_RUN) * i);
2728 
2729  ExFreePool (Memory);
2730  Memory = Memory2;
2731  }
2732  }
2733  }
2734

2736  Memory->NumberOfPages = TotalPages;
2737

2739 }

3629  //
3630 
3631  MiCreateBitMap (&MmPagedPoolInfo.PagedPoolAllocationMap, Size, NonPagedPool);
3632  RtlSetAllBits (MmPagedPoolInfo.PagedPoolAllocationMap);
3633 
3634  //
3635  // Indicate first page worth of PTEs are available.
3636  //
3637 
3638  RtlClearBits (MmPagedPoolInfo.PagedPoolAllocationMap, 0, PTE_PER_PAGE);
3639 
3640  MiCreateBitMap (&MmPagedPoolInfo.EndOfPagedPoolBitmap, Size, NonPagedPool);
3641  RtlClearAllBits (MmPagedPoolInfo.EndOfPagedPoolBitmap);
3642 
3643  //
3644  // If verifier is present then build the verifier paged pool bitmap.
3645  //
3646 
3647  if (MmVerifyDriverBufferLength != (ULONG)-1) {
3648  MiCreateBitMap (&VerifierLargePagedPoolMap, Size, NonPagedPool);
3649  RtlClearAllBits (VerifierLargePagedPoolMap);
3650  }
3651 
3652  //
3653  // Initialize paged pool.
3654  //
3655 
3656  InitializePool (PagedPool, 0L);
3657 
3658  //
3659  // If paged pool is really nonpageable then allocate the memory now.
3660  //
3661 
3662  if (MmDisablePagingExecutive & MM_PAGED_POOL_LOCKED_DOWN) {
3663 
3664  PointerPde = MiGetPdeAddress (MmPagedPoolStart);
3665  PointerPde += 1;
3666  LastPde = MiGetPdeAddress (MmPagedPoolEnd);
3667  TempPte = ValidKernelPde;
3668 
3669  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (MmPagedPoolStart);
3670  LastPte = MiGetPteAddress (MmPagedPoolEnd);
3671 
3672  ASSERT (MmPagedPoolCommit == 0);
3673  MmPagedPoolCommit = (ULONG)(LastPte - PointerPte + 1);
3674 
3675  ASSERT (MmPagedPoolInfo.PagedPoolCommit == 0);
3676  MmPagedPoolInfo.PagedPoolCommit = MmPagedPoolCommit;
3677 
3678 #if DBG
3679  //
3680  // Ensure no paged pool has been allocated yet.
3681  //
3682 
3683  for (i = 0; i < PTE_PER_PAGE; i += 1) {
3684  ASSERT (!RtlCheckBit (MmPagedPoolInfo.PagedPoolAllocationMap, i));
3685  }
3686 
3687  while (i < MmSizeOfPagedPoolInBytes / PAGE_SIZE) {
3688  ASSERT (RtlCheckBit (MmPagedPoolInfo.PagedPoolAllocationMap, i));
3689  i += 1;
3690  }
3691 #endif
3692 
3693  RtlClearAllBits (MmPagedPoolInfo.PagedPoolAllocationMap);
3694 
3695  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
3696 
3697  //
3698  // Map in the page table pages.
3699  //
3700 
3701  MmResidentAvailablePages -= (LastPde - PointerPde + 1);
3702  AdditionalCommittedPages += (LastPde - PointerPde + 1);
3703 
3704  while (PointerPde <= LastPde) {
3705 
3706  ASSERT (PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
3707 
3708  PageFrameIndex = MiRemoveZeroPage(
3709  MI_GET_PAGE_COLOR_FROM_PTE (PointerPde));
3710  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = PageFrameIndex;
3711  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPde, TempPte);
3712 
3713 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
3714  ContainingFrame = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE(MiGetPteAddress (PointerPde));
3715 #else
3716  ContainingFrame = MmSystemPageDirectory[(PointerPde - MiGetPdeAddress(0)) / PDE_PER_PAGE];
3717 #endif
3718 
3719  MiInitializePfnForOtherProcess (PageFrameIndex,
3720  MiGetPteAddress (PointerPde),
3721  ContainingFrame);
3722 
3723  PointerPde += 1;
3724  }
3725 
3726  MmPagedPoolInfo.NextPdeForPagedPoolExpansion = PointerPde;
3727 
3728  TempPte = ValidKernelPte;
3729  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte);
3730 
3731  ASSERT (MmAvailablePages > (PFN_COUNT)(LastPte - PointerPte + 1));
3732  ASSERT (MmResidentAvailablePages > (SPFN_NUMBER)(LastPte - PointerPte + 1));
3733  MmResidentAvailablePages -= (LastPte - PointerPte + 1);
3734  AdditionalCommittedPages += (LastPte - PointerPte + 1);
3735 
3736  while (PointerPte <= LastPte) {
3737 
3738  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
3739 
3740  PageFrameIndex = MiRemoveAnyPage(
3741  MI_GET_PAGE_COLOR_FROM_PTE (PointerPte));
3742  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = PageFrameIndex;
3743 
3744  MiInitializePfnAndMakePteValid (PageFrameIndex, PointerPte, TempPte);
3745 
3746  PointerPte += 1;
3747  }
3748 
3749  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
3750  }
3751 
3752  //
3753  // Since the commitment return path is lock free, the total committed
3754  // page count must be atomically incremented.
3755  //
3756 
3757  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MmTotalCommittedPages, AdditionalCommittedPages);
3758 
3759  MiInitializeSpecialPool (NonPagedPool);
3760 
3761  //
3762  // Initialize the default paged pool signaling thresholds.
3763  //
3764 
3765  MiLowPagedPoolThreshold = (30 * 1024 * 1024) >> PAGE_SHIFT;
3766 
3767  if ((Size / 5) < MiLowPagedPoolThreshold) {
3768  MiLowPagedPoolThreshold = Size / 5;
3769  }
3770 
3771  MiHighPagedPoolThreshold = (60 * 1024 * 1024) >> PAGE_SHIFT;
3772 
3773  if (((Size * 2) / 5) < MiHighPagedPoolThreshold) {
3774  MiHighPagedPoolThreshold = (Size * 2) / 5;
3775  }
3776 
3777  ASSERT (MiLowPagedPoolThreshold < MiHighPagedPoolThreshold);
3778 
3779  //
3780  // Allow mapping of views into system space.
3781  //
3782 
3783  MiInitializeSystemSpaceMap (NULL);
3784 
3785  return;
3786 }

3842 VOID
3843 MiFindInitializationCode (
3844  OUT PVOID *StartVa,
3845  OUT PVOID *EndVa
3846  )
3847 
3848 /*++
3849 
3850 Routine Description:
3851 
3852  This function locates the start and end of the initialization code for
3853  each loaded module list entry. This code resides in the INIT section
3854  of each image.
3855 
3856 Arguments:
3857 
3858  StartVa - Returns the starting address of the init section.
3859 
3860  EndVa - Returns the ending address of the init section.
3861 
3862 Return Value:
3863 
3864  None.
3865 
3866 Environment:
3867 
3868  Kernel Mode Only. End of system initialization.
3869 
3870 --*/
3871 
3872 {
3873  ULONG Span;
3874  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY LdrDataTableEntry;
3875  PVOID CurrentBase;
3876  PVOID InitStart;
3877  PVOID InitEnd;
3878  PLIST_ENTRY Next;
3879  PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS NtHeader;
3880  PIMAGE_SECTION_HEADER SectionTableEntry;
3881  PIMAGE_SECTION_HEADER LastDiscard;
3882  LONG i;
3883  LOGICAL DiscardSection;
3884  PVOID MiFindInitializationCodeAddress;
3885  PKTHREAD CurrentThread;
3886  UNICODE_STRING NameString;
3887 
3888  MiFindInitializationCodeAddress = MmGetProcedureAddress((PVOID)(ULONG_PTR)&MiFindInitializationCode);
3889 
3890  *StartVa = NULL;
3891 
3892  //
3893  // Walk through the loader blocks looking for the base which
3894  // contains this routine.
3895  //
3896 
3897  CurrentThread = KeGetCurrentThread ();
3898  KeEnterCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
3899 
3900  //
3901  // Acquire the load lock to ensure that we don't slice into a load
3902  // in progress (ie: fixups on INIT code may be ongoing) on a driver
3903  // already in the list.
3904  //
3905 
3906  KeWaitForSingleObject (&MmSystemLoadLock,
3907  WrVirtualMemory,
3908  KernelMode,
3909  FALSE,
3910  (PLARGE_INTEGER)NULL);
3911 
3912  ExAcquireResourceExclusiveLite (&PsLoadedModuleResource, TRUE);
3913 
3914  Next = PsLoadedModuleList.Flink;
3915 
3916  while (Next != &PsLoadedModuleList) {
3917  LdrDataTableEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD (Next,
3918  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
3919  InLoadOrderLinks);
3920 
3921  if (LdrDataTableEntry->Flags & LDRP_MM_LOADED) {
3922 
3923  //
3924  // This entry was loaded by MmLoadSystemImage so it's already
3925  // had its init section removed.
3926  //
3927 
3928  Next = Next->Flink;
3929  continue;
3930  }
3931 
3932  CurrentBase = (PVOID)LdrDataTableEntry->DllBase;
3933  NtHeader = RtlImageNtHeader (CurrentBase);
3934 
3935  if (NtHeader == NULL) {
3936  Next = Next->Flink;
3937  continue;
3938  }
3939 
3940  SectionTableEntry = (PIMAGE_SECTION_HEADER)((PCHAR)NtHeader +
3941  sizeof(ULONG) +
3942  sizeof(IMAGE_FILE_HEADER) +
3943  NtHeader->FileHeader.SizeOfOptionalHeader);
3944 
3945  //
3946  // From the image header, locate the sections named 'INIT',
3947  // PAGEVRF* and PAGESPEC. INIT always goes, the others go depending
3948  // on registry configuration.
3949  //
3950 
3951  i = NtHeader->FileHeader.NumberOfSections;
3952 
3953  InitStart = NULL;
3954  while (i > 0) {
3955 
3956 #if DBG
3957  if ((*(PULONG)SectionTableEntry->Name == 'tini') ||
3958  (*(PULONG)SectionTableEntry->Name == 'egap')) {
3959  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_INFO_LEVEL,
3960  "driver %wZ has lower case sections (init or pagexxx)\n",
3961  &LdrDataTableEntry->FullDllName);
3962  }
3963 #endif
3964 
3965  DiscardSection = FALSE;
3966 
3967  //
3968  // Free any INIT sections (or relocation sections that haven't
3969  // been already). Note a driver may have a relocation section
3970  // but not have any INIT code.
3971  //
3972 
3973  if ((*(PULONG)SectionTableEntry->Name == 'TINI') ||
3974  ((SectionTableEntry->Characteristics & IMAGE_SCN_MEM_DISCARDABLE) != 0)) {
3975  DiscardSection = TRUE;
3976  }
3977  else if (*(PULONG)SectionTableEntry->Name == 'EGAP') {
3978 
3979  if ((SectionTableEntry->Name[4] == 'V') &&
3980  (SectionTableEntry->Name[5] == 'R') &&
3981  (SectionTableEntry->Name[6] == 'F')) {
3982 
3983  //
3984  // Discard PAGEVRF* if no drivers are being instrumented.
3985  //
3986 
3987  if (MmVerifyDriverBufferLength == (ULONG)-1) {
3988  DiscardSection = TRUE;
3989  }
3990  }
3991  else if (*(PULONG)&SectionTableEntry->Name[4] == 'CEPS') {
3992 
3993  //
3994  // Discard PAGESPEC special pool code if it's not enabled.
3995  //
3996 
3997  if (MiSpecialPoolFirstPte == NULL) {
3998  DiscardSection = TRUE;
3999  }
4000  }
4001  }
4002 
4003  if (DiscardSection == TRUE) {
4004 
4005  InitStart = (PVOID)((PCHAR)CurrentBase + SectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress);
4006  //
4007  // Generally, SizeOfRawData is larger than VirtualSize for each
4008  // section because it includes the padding to get to the
4009  // subsection alignment boundary. However, if the image is
4010  // linked with subsection alignment == native page alignment,
4011  // the linker will have VirtualSize be much larger than
4012  // SizeOfRawData because it will account for all the bss.
4013  //
4014 
4015  Span = SectionTableEntry->SizeOfRawData;
4016 
4017  if (Span < SectionTableEntry->Misc.VirtualSize) {
4018  Span = SectionTableEntry->Misc.VirtualSize;
4019  }
4020  InitEnd = (PVOID)((PCHAR)InitStart + Span - 1);
4021  InitEnd = (PVOID)((PCHAR)PAGE_ALIGN ((PCHAR)InitEnd +
4022  (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.SectionAlignment - 1)) - 1);
4023  InitStart = (PVOID)ROUND_TO_PAGES (InitStart);
4024 
4025  //
4026  // Check if more sections are discardable after this one so
4027  // even small INIT sections can be discarded.
4028  //
4029 
4030  if (i == 1) {
4031  LastDiscard = SectionTableEntry;
4032  }
4033  else {
4034  LastDiscard = NULL;
4035  do {
4036  i -= 1;
4037  SectionTableEntry += 1;
4038 
4039  if ((SectionTableEntry->Characteristics &
4040  IMAGE_SCN_MEM_DISCARDABLE) != 0) {
4041 
4042  //
4043  // Discard this too.
4044  //
4045 
4046  LastDiscard = SectionTableEntry;
4047  }
4048  else {
4049  break;
4050  }
4051  } while (i > 1);
4052  }
4053 
4054  if (LastDiscard) {
4055  //
4056  // Generally, SizeOfRawData is larger than VirtualSize for each
4057  // section because it includes the padding to get to the subsection
4058  // alignment boundary. However, if the image is linked with
4059  // subsection alignment == native page alignment, the linker will
4060  // have VirtualSize be much larger than SizeOfRawData because it
4061  // will account for all the bss.
4062  //
4063 
4064  Span = LastDiscard->SizeOfRawData;
4065 
4066  if (Span < LastDiscard->Misc.VirtualSize) {
4067  Span = LastDiscard->Misc.VirtualSize;
4068  }
4069 
4070  InitEnd = (PVOID)(((PCHAR)CurrentBase +
4071  LastDiscard->VirtualAddress) +
4072  (Span - 1));
4073 
4074  //
4075  // If this isn't the last section in the driver then the
4076  // the next section is not discardable. So the last
4077  // section is not rounded down, but all others must be.
4078  //
4079 
4080  if (i != 1) {
4081  InitEnd = (PVOID)((PCHAR)PAGE_ALIGN ((PCHAR)InitEnd +
4082  (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.SectionAlignment - 1)) - 1);
4083  }
4084  }
4085 
4086  if (InitEnd > (PVOID)((PCHAR)CurrentBase +
4087  LdrDataTableEntry->SizeOfImage)) {
4088  InitEnd = (PVOID)(((ULONG_PTR)CurrentBase +
4089  (LdrDataTableEntry->SizeOfImage - 1)) |
4090  (PAGE_SIZE - 1));
4091  }
4092 
4093  if (InitStart <= InitEnd) {
4094  if ((MiFindInitializationCodeAddress >= InitStart) &&
4095  (MiFindInitializationCodeAddress <= InitEnd)) {
4096 
4097  //
4098  // This init section is in the kernel, don't free it
4099  // now as it would free this code!
4100  //
4101 
4102  ASSERT (*StartVa == NULL);
4103  *StartVa = InitStart;
4104  *EndVa = InitEnd;
4105  }
4106  else {
4107 
4108  //
4109  // Don't free the INIT code for a driver mapped by
4110  // large pages because if it unloads later, we'd have
4111  // to deal with discontiguous ranges of pages to free.
4112  // There would also be the issue of the frames getting
4113  // given out and mapped with a conflicting TB attribute
4114  // as well ...
4115  //
4116  // Make a special exception for the kernel & HAL
4117  // since those never unload.
4118  //
4119 
4120  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (InitStart)) {
4121 
4122  NameString.Buffer = (const PUSHORT) KERNEL_NAME;
4123  NameString.Length = sizeof (KERNEL_NAME) - sizeof (WCHAR);
4124  NameString.MaximumLength = sizeof KERNEL_NAME;
4125 
4126  if (!RtlEqualUnicodeString (&NameString,
4127  &LdrDataTableEntry->BaseDllName,
4128  TRUE)) {
4129  MiFreeInitializationCode (InitStart, InitEnd);
4130  }
4131 
4132  NameString.Buffer = (const PUSHORT) HAL_NAME;
4133  NameString.Length = sizeof (HAL_NAME) - sizeof (WCHAR);
4134  NameString.MaximumLength = sizeof HAL_NAME;
4135 
4136  if (!RtlEqualUnicodeString (&NameString,
4137  &LdrDataTableEntry->BaseDllName,
4138  TRUE)) {
4139  MiFreeInitializationCode (InitStart, InitEnd);
4140  }
4141  }
4142  else {
4143  MiFreeInitializationCode (InitStart, InitEnd);
4144  }
4145  }
4146  }
4147  }
4148  i -= 1;
4149  SectionTableEntry += 1;
4150  }
4151  Next = Next->Flink;
4152  }
4153 
4154  ExReleaseResourceLite (&PsLoadedModuleResource);
4155 
4156  KeReleaseMutant (&MmSystemLoadLock, 1, FALSE, FALSE);
4157 
4158  KeLeaveCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
4159 
4160  return;
4161 }

4164 VOID
4165 MiFreeInitializationCode (
4166  IN PVOID StartVa,
4167  IN PVOID EndVa
4168  )
4169 
4170 /*++
4171 
4172 Routine Description:
4173 
4174  This function is called to delete the initialization code for each
4175  loaded module list entry.
4176 
4177 Arguments:
4178 
4179  StartVa - Supplies the starting address of the range to delete.
4180 
4181  EndVa - Supplies the ending address of the range to delete.
4182 
4183 Return Value:
4184 
4185  None.
4186 
4187 Environment:
4188 
4189  Kernel Mode Only. Runs after system initialization.
4190 
4191 --*/
4192 
4193 {
4194  PMMPTE PointerPte;
4195  PFN_NUMBER PagesFreed;
4196  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
4197 
4198  ASSERT (ExPageLockHandle);
4199 
4200 #if defined (_MI_MORE_THAN_4GB_)
4201  if (MiNoLowMemory != 0) {
4202 
4203  //
4204  // Don't free this range as the kernel is always below the memory
4205  // threshold configured for this system.
4206  //
4207 
4208  return;
4209  }
4210 #endif
4211 
4212  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (StartVa);
4213 
4214  PagesFreed = (PFN_NUMBER) (1 + MiGetPteAddress (EndVa) - PointerPte);
4215 
4216  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (StartVa)) {
4217 
4218  //
4219  // Don't put these frames on the general purpose freelist because
4220  // they lie inside a range being mapped with a large page (or
4221  // otherwise locked down TB entry). Thus we must ensure that
4222  // these are always mapped cached to avoid TB attribute conflict
4223  // problems.
4224  //
4225 
4226  PageFrameIndex = MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN (StartVa);
4227 
4228  MiAddExpansionNonPagedPool (PageFrameIndex, PagesFreed, FALSE);
4229  }
4230  else {
4231  PagesFreed = MiDeleteSystemPageableVm (PointerPte,
4232  PagesFreed,
4233  MI_DELETE_FLUSH_TB,
4234  NULL);
4235  }
4236 
4237  if (PagesFreed != 0) {
4238  MiReturnCommitment (PagesFreed);
4239  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (PagesFreed,
4240  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_UNLOAD_SYSTEM_IMAGE1);
4241  }
4242 
4243  return;
4244 }

4381 
4382  StartSectionTableEntry = NULL;
4383  SectionTableEntry = (PIMAGE_SECTION_HEADER)((PCHAR)NtHeader +
4384  sizeof(ULONG) +
4385  sizeof(IMAGE_FILE_HEADER) +
4386  NtHeader->FileHeader.SizeOfOptionalHeader);
4387 
4388  //
4389  // From the image header, locate the section named 'PAGE' or '.edata'.
4390  //
4391 
4392  i = NtHeader->FileHeader.NumberOfSections;
4393 
4394  PointerPte = NULL;
4395 
4396  while (i > 0) {
4397 
4398  SectionBaseAddress = SECTION_BASE_ADDRESS(SectionTableEntry);
4399 
4400  if ((PUCHAR)SectionBaseAddress ==
4401  ((PUCHAR)CurrentBase + SectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress)) {
4402  AlreadyLockedOnce = TRUE;
4403 
4404  //
4405  // This subsection has already been locked down (and possibly
4406  // unlocked as well) at least once. If it is NOT locked down
4407  // right now and the pages are not in the system working set
4408  // then include it in the chunk to be paged.
4409  //
4410 
4411  SectionLockCountPointer = SECTION_LOCK_COUNT_POINTER (SectionTableEntry);
4412 
4413  if (*SectionLockCountPointer == 0) {
4414 
4415  SubsectionStartPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PVOID)(ROUND_TO_PAGES (
4416  (ULONG_PTR)CurrentBase +
4417  SectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress)));
4418 
4419  //
4420  // Generally, SizeOfRawData is larger than VirtualSize
4421  // for each section because it includes the padding to
4422  // get to the subsection alignment boundary. However,
4423  // if the image is linked with subsection alignment ==
4424  // native page alignment, the linker will have VirtualSize
4425  // be much larger than SizeOfRawData because it
4426  // will account for all the bss.
4427  //
4428 
4429  Span = SectionTableEntry->SizeOfRawData;
4430 
4431  if (Span < SectionTableEntry->Misc.VirtualSize) {
4432  Span = SectionTableEntry->Misc.VirtualSize;
4433  }
4434 
4435  SubsectionLastPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)CurrentBase +
4436  SectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress +
4437  (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.SectionAlignment - 1) +
4438  Span -
4439  PAGE_SIZE));
4440 
4441  if (SubsectionLastPte >= SubsectionStartPte) {
4442  AlreadyLockedOnce = FALSE;
4443  }
4444  }
4445  }
4446  else {
4447  AlreadyLockedOnce = FALSE;
4448  }
4449 
4450  PageSection = ((*(PULONG)SectionTableEntry->Name == 'EGAP') ||
4451  (*(PULONG)SectionTableEntry->Name == 'ade.')) &&
4452  (AlreadyLockedOnce == FALSE);
4453 
4454  if (*(PULONG)SectionTableEntry->Name == 'EGAP') {
4455 
4456  if ((SectionTableEntry->Name[4] == 'K') &&
4457  (SectionTableEntry->Name[5] == 'D')) {
4458 
4459  //
4460  // Only pageout PAGEKD if KdPitchDebugger is TRUE.
4461  //
4462 
4463  PageSection = KdPitchDebugger;
4464  }
4465  else if ((SectionTableEntry->Name[4] == 'V') &&
4466  (SectionTableEntry->Name[5] == 'R') &&
4467  (SectionTableEntry->Name[6] == 'F')) {
4468 
4469  //
4470  // Pageout PAGEVRF* if no drivers are being instrumented.
4471  //
4472 
4473  if (MmVerifyDriverBufferLength != (ULONG)-1) {
4474  PageSection = FALSE;
4475  }
4476  }
4477  else if (*(PULONG)&SectionTableEntry->Name[4] == 'CEPS') {
4478 
4479  //
4480  // Pageout PAGESPEC special pool code if it's not enabled.
4481  //
4482 
4483  if (MiSpecialPoolFirstPte != NULL) {
4484  PageSection = FALSE;
4485  }
4486  }
4487  }
4488 
4489  if (PageSection) {
4490 
4491  //
4492  // This section is pageable, save away the start and end.
4493  //
4494 
4495  if (PointerPte == NULL) {
4496 
4497  //
4498  // Previous section was NOT pageable, get the start address.
4499  //
4500 
4501  ASSERT (StartSectionTableEntry == NULL);
4502  StartSectionTableEntry = SectionTableEntry;
4503  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PVOID)(ROUND_TO_PAGES (
4504  (ULONG_PTR)CurrentBase +
4505  SectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress)));
4506  }
4507 
4508  //
4509  // Generally, SizeOfRawData is larger than VirtualSize for each
4510  // section because it includes the padding to get to the
4511  // subsection alignment boundary. However, if the image is
4512  // linked with subsection alignment == native page alignment,
4513  // the linker will have VirtualSize be much larger than
4514  // SizeOfRawData because it will account for all the bss.
4515  //
4516 
4517  Span = SectionTableEntry->SizeOfRawData;
4518 
4519  if (Span < SectionTableEntry->Misc.VirtualSize) {
4520  Span = SectionTableEntry->Misc.VirtualSize;
4521  }
4522 
4523  LastPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)CurrentBase +
4524  SectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress +
4525  (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.SectionAlignment - 1) +
4526  Span - PAGE_SIZE));
4527  }
4528  else {
4529 
4530  //
4531  // This section is not pageable, if the previous section was
4532  // pageable, enable it.
4533  //
4534 
4535  if (PointerPte != NULL) {
4536 
4537  ASSERT (StartSectionTableEntry != NULL);
4538  LOCK_SYSTEM_WS (CurrentThread);
4539  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4540 
4541  StartVa = PAGE_ALIGN (StartSectionTableEntry);
4542  while (StartVa < (PVOID) SectionTableEntry) {
4543 
4544  Waited = MiMakeSystemAddressValidPfnSystemWs (StartVa, OldIrql);
4545 
4546  if (Waited != 0) {
4547 
4548  //
4549  // Restart at the top as the locks were released.
4550  //
4551 
4552  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4553  UNLOCK_SYSTEM_WS (CurrentThread);
4554  goto restart;
4555  }
4556  StartVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR)StartVa + PAGE_SIZE);
4557  }
4558 
4559  //
4560  // Now that we're holding the proper locks, rewalk all
4561  // the sections to make sure they weren't locked down
4562  // after we checked above.
4563  //
4564 
4565  while (StartSectionTableEntry < SectionTableEntry) {
4566  SectionBaseAddress = SECTION_BASE_ADDRESS(StartSectionTableEntry);
4567 
4568  SectionLockCountPointer = SECTION_LOCK_COUNT_POINTER (StartSectionTableEntry);
4569  if (((PUCHAR)SectionBaseAddress ==
4570  ((PUCHAR)CurrentBase + StartSectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress)) &&
4571  (*SectionLockCountPointer != 0)) {
4572 
4573  //
4574  // Restart at the top as the section has been
4575  // explicitly locked by a driver since we first
4576  // checked above.
4577  //
4578 
4579  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4580  UNLOCK_SYSTEM_WS (CurrentThread);
4581  goto restart;
4582  }
4583  StartSectionTableEntry += 1;
4584  }
4585 
4586  MiEnablePagingOfDriverAtInit (PointerPte, LastPte);
4587 
4588  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4589  UNLOCK_SYSTEM_WS (CurrentThread);
4590 
4591  PointerPte = NULL;
4592  StartSectionTableEntry = NULL;
4593  }
4594  }
4595  i -= 1;
4596  SectionTableEntry += 1;
4597  }
4598 
4599  if (PointerPte != NULL) {
4600  ASSERT (StartSectionTableEntry != NULL);
4601  LOCK_SYSTEM_WS (CurrentThread);
4602  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4603 
4604  StartVa = PAGE_ALIGN (StartSectionTableEntry);
4605  while (StartVa < (PVOID) SectionTableEntry) {
4606 
4607  Waited = MiMakeSystemAddressValidPfnSystemWs (StartVa, OldIrql);
4608 
4609  if (Waited != 0) {
4610 
4611  //
4612  // Restart at the top as the locks were released.
4613  //
4614 
4615  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4616  UNLOCK_SYSTEM_WS (CurrentThread);
4617  goto restart;
4618  }
4619  StartVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR)StartVa + PAGE_SIZE);
4620  }
4621 
4622  //
4623  // Now that we're holding the proper locks, rewalk all
4624  // the sections to make sure they weren't locked down
4625  // after we checked above.
4626  //
4627 
4628  while (StartSectionTableEntry < SectionTableEntry) {
4629  SectionBaseAddress = SECTION_BASE_ADDRESS(StartSectionTableEntry);
4630 
4631  SectionLockCountPointer = SECTION_LOCK_COUNT_POINTER (StartSectionTableEntry);
4632  if (((PUCHAR)SectionBaseAddress ==
4633  ((PUCHAR)CurrentBase + StartSectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress)) &&
4634  (*SectionLockCountPointer != 0)) {
4635 
4636  //
4637  // Restart at the top as the section has been
4638  // explicitly locked by a driver since we first
4639  // checked above.
4640  //
4641 
4642  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4643  UNLOCK_SYSTEM_WS (CurrentThread);
4644  goto restart;
4645  }
4646  StartSectionTableEntry += 1;
4647  }
4648  MiEnablePagingOfDriverAtInit (PointerPte, LastPte);
4649 
4650  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4651  UNLOCK_SYSTEM_WS (CurrentThread);
4652  }
4653 
4654  Next = Next->Flink;
4655  }
4656 
4657  ExReleaseResourceLite (&PsLoadedModuleResource);
4658 
4659  KeReleaseMutant (&MmSystemLoadLock, 1, FALSE, FALSE);
4660 
4661  KeLeaveCriticalRegionThread (&CurrentThread->Tcb);
4662 
4663  return;
4664 }

4666 
4667 VOID
4668 MiEnablePagingOfDriverAtInit (
4669  IN PMMPTE PointerPte,
4670  IN PMMPTE LastPte
4671  )
4672 
4673 /*++
4674 
4675 Routine Description:
4676 
4677  This routine marks the specified range of PTEs as pageable.
4678 
4679 Arguments:
4680 
4681  PointerPte - Supplies the starting PTE.
4682 
4683  LastPte - Supplies the ending PTE.
4684 
4685 Return Value:
4686 
4687  None.
4688 
4689 Environment:
4690 
4691  Working set pushlock AND PFN lock held.
4692 
4693 --*/
4694 
4695 {
4696  PVOID Base;
4697  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
4698  PMMPFN Pfn;
4699  MMPTE TempPte;
4700  LOGICAL SessionAddress;
4701  ULONG FlushCount;
4702  PVOID VaFlushList[MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT];
4703 
4704  FlushCount = 0;
4705 
4706  MM_PFN_LOCK_ASSERT();
4707 
4708  Base = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
4709  SessionAddress = MI_IS_SESSION_PTE (PointerPte);
4710 
4711  while (PointerPte <= LastPte) {
4712 
4713  //
4714  // The PTE must be carefully checked as drivers may call MmPageEntire
4715  // during their DriverEntry yet faults may occur prior to this routine
4716  // running which cause pages to already be resident and in the working
4717  // set at this point. So checks for validity and wsindex must be
4718  // applied.
4719  //
4720 
4721  if (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
4722  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
4723  Pfn = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
4724  ASSERT (Pfn->u2.ShareCount == 1);
4725 
4726  if (Pfn->u1.WsIndex == 0) {
4727 
4728  //
4729  // Set the working set index to zero. This allows page table
4730  // pages to be brought back in with the proper WSINDEX.
4731  //
4732 
4733  MI_ZERO_WSINDEX (Pfn);
4734 
4735  //
4736  // Original PTE may need to be set for drivers loaded via
4737  // ntldr.
4738  //
4739 
4740  if (Pfn->OriginalPte.u.Long == 0) {
4741  Pfn->OriginalPte.u.Long = MM_KERNEL_DEMAND_ZERO_PTE;
4742  Pfn->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Protection |= MM_EXECUTE;
4743  }
4744 
4745  MI_SET_MODIFIED (Pfn, 1, 0x11);
4746 
4747  TempPte = *PointerPte;
4748 
4749  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE_TRANSITION (TempPte,
4750  Pfn->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Protection);
4751 
4752  MI_WRITE_INVALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte);
4753 
4754  if (FlushCount < MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
4755  VaFlushList[FlushCount] = Base;
4756  FlushCount += 1;
4757  }
4758 
4759  //
4760  // Flush the TB and decrement the number of valid PTEs
4761  // within the containing page table page. Note that for a
4762  // private page, the page table page is still needed because
4763  // the page is in transition.
4764  //
4765 
4766  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn, PageFrameIndex);
4767 
4768  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (1, MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_PAGE_DRIVER);
4769 
4770  MmTotalSystemCodePages += 1;
4771  }
4772  else {
4773 
4774  //
4775  // This would need to be taken out of the WSLEs so skip it for
4776  // now and let the normal paging algorithms remove it if we
4777  // run into memory pressure.
4778  //
4779  }
4780 
4781  }
4782  Base = (PVOID)((PCHAR)Base + PAGE_SIZE);
4783  PointerPte += 1;
4784  }
4785 
4786  if (FlushCount == 0) {
4787  NOTHING;
4788  }
4789  else if (FlushCount == 1) {
4790  MI_FLUSH_SINGLE_TB (VaFlushList[0], TRUE);
4791  }
4792  else if (FlushCount < MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
4793  MI_FLUSH_MULTIPLE_TB (FlushCount, &VaFlushList[0], TRUE);
4794  }
4795  else {
4796  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB (0x15);
4797  }
4798 
4799  return;
4800 }

4842 // PFN lock is held.

4865  KeClearEvent (MiLowMemoryEvent);
4866  }
4867  }

4869  if (KeReadStateEvent (MiHighMemoryEvent) == 0) {
4870  KeSetEvent (MiHighMemoryEvent, 0, FALSE);
4871  }
4872

4881 LOGICAL
4882 MiInitializeMemoryEvents (
4883  VOID
4884  )
4885 {
4886  KIRQL OldIrql;
4887  NTSTATUS Status;
4888  UNICODE_STRING LowMem = CONSTANT_UNICODE_STRING(L"\\KernelObjects\\LowMemoryCondition");
4889  UNICODE_STRING HighMem = CONSTANT_UNICODE_STRING(L"\\KernelObjects\\HighMemoryCondition");
4890  UNICODE_STRING LowPagedPoolMem = CONSTANT_UNICODE_STRING(L"\\KernelObjects\\LowPagedPoolCondition");
4891  UNICODE_STRING HighPagedPoolMem = CONSTANT_UNICODE_STRING(L"\\KernelObjects\\HighPagedPoolCondition");
4892  UNICODE_STRING LowNonPagedPoolMem = CONSTANT_UNICODE_STRING(L"\\KernelObjects\\LowNonPagedPoolCondition");
4893  UNICODE_STRING HighNonPagedPoolMem = CONSTANT_UNICODE_STRING(L"\\KernelObjects\\HighNonPagedPoolCondition");
4894 
4895  //
4896  // The thresholds may be set in the registry, if so, they are interpreted
4897  // in megabytes so convert them to pages now.
4898  //
4899  // If the user modifies the registry to introduce his own values, don't
4900  // bother error checking them as they can't hurt the system regardless (bad
4901  // values just may result in events not getting signaled or staying
4902  // signaled when they shouldn't, but that's not fatal).
4903  //
4904 
4905  if (MmLowMemoryThreshold != 0) {
4906  MmLowMemoryThreshold *= ((1024 * 1024) / PAGE_SIZE);
4907  }
4908  else {
4909 
4910  //
4911  // Scale the threshold so on servers the low threshold is
4912  // approximately 32MB per 4GB, capping it at 64MB.
4913  //
4914 
4915  MmLowMemoryThreshold = MmPlentyFreePages;
4916 
4917  if (MmNumberOfPhysicalPages > 0x40000) {
4918  MmLowMemoryThreshold = (32 * 1024 * 1024) / PAGE_SIZE;
4919  MmLowMemoryThreshold += ((MmNumberOfPhysicalPages - 0x40000) >> 7);
4920  }
4921  else if (MmNumberOfPhysicalPages > 0x8000) {
4922  MmLowMemoryThreshold += ((MmNumberOfPhysicalPages - 0x8000) >> 5);
4923  }
4924 
4925  if (MmLowMemoryThreshold > (64 * 1024 * 1024) / PAGE_SIZE) {
4926  MmLowMemoryThreshold = (64 * 1024 * 1024) / PAGE_SIZE;
4927  }
4928  }
4929 
4930  if (MmHighMemoryThreshold != 0) {
4931  MmHighMemoryThreshold *= ((1024 * 1024) / PAGE_SIZE);
4932  }
4933  else {
4934  MmHighMemoryThreshold = 3 * MmLowMemoryThreshold;
4935  ASSERT (MmHighMemoryThreshold > MmLowMemoryThreshold);
4936  }
4937 
4938  if (MmHighMemoryThreshold < MmLowMemoryThreshold) {
4939  MmHighMemoryThreshold = MmLowMemoryThreshold;
4940  }
4941 
4942  Status = MiCreateMemoryEvent (&LowMem, &MiLowMemoryEvent);
4943 
4944  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
4945 #if DBG
4946  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
4947  "MM: Memory event initialization failed %x\n", Status);
4948 #endif
4949  return FALSE;
4950  }
4951 
4952  Status = MiCreateMemoryEvent (&HighMem, &MiHighMemoryEvent);
4953 
4954  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
4955 #if DBG
4956  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
4957  "MM: Memory event initialization failed %x\n", Status);
4958 #endif
4959  return FALSE;
4960  }
4961 
4962  //
4963  // Create the events for the pool thresholds.
4964  //
4965 
4966  Status = MiCreateMemoryEvent (&LowPagedPoolMem, &MiLowPagedPoolEvent);
4967 
4968  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
4969 #if DBG
4970  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
4971  "MM: Memory event initialization failed %x\n", Status);
4972 #endif
4973  return FALSE;
4974  }
4975 
4976  Status = MiCreateMemoryEvent (&HighPagedPoolMem, &MiHighPagedPoolEvent);
4977 
4978  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
4979 #if DBG
4980  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
4981  "MM: Memory event initialization failed %x\n", Status);
4982 #endif
4983  return FALSE;
4984  }
4985 
4986  Status = MiCreateMemoryEvent (&LowNonPagedPoolMem, &MiLowNonPagedPoolEvent);
4987 
4988  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
4989 #if DBG
4990  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
4991  "MM: Memory event initialization failed %x\n", Status);
4992 #endif
4993  return FALSE;
4994  }
4995 
4996  Status = MiCreateMemoryEvent (&HighNonPagedPoolMem, &MiHighNonPagedPoolEvent);
4997 
4998  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
4999 #if DBG
5000  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
5001  "MM: Memory event initialization failed %x\n", Status);
5002 #endif
5003  return FALSE;
5004  }
5005 
5006  //
5007  // Initialize the pool threshold events based on the current system
5008  // values.
5009  //
5010 
5011  MiInitializePoolEvents ();
5012 
5013  //
5014  // Initialize the event values.
5015  //
5016 
5017  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5018 
5019  MiNotifyMemoryEvents ();
5020 
5021  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5022 
5023  return TRUE;
5024 }

5080

5082  ExFreePool (Dacl);

5084  }

5088  EVENT_ALL_ACCESS,
5089  SeLocalSystemSid);
5090

5092  ExFreePool (Dacl);
5093  return Status;

5098  TRUE,
5099  Dacl,
5100  FALSE);
5101 
5102  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
5103  ExFreePool (Dacl);
5104  return Status;
5105  }
5106 
5107  InitializeObjectAttributes (&ObjectAttributes,
5108  EventName,
5109  OBJ_KERNEL_HANDLE | OBJ_PERMANENT,
5110  NULL,
5111  &SecurityDescriptor);
5112 
5113  Status = ZwCreateEvent (&EventHandle,
5114  EVENT_ALL_ACCESS,
5115  &ObjectAttributes,

5222 Routine Description:
5223 
5224  This function scans the page directory and page tables for HAL I/O space
5225  mappings so they can be added to the page attribute table (to prevent
5226  any subsequent mappings from using a conflicting attribute). This also

5233

5240  Kernel mode, Phase 0 only.

5262

5264

5266

5268 
5269  if ((PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 1) &&
5270  (PointerPde->u.Hard.LargePage == 0)) {
5271

5273

5275 
5276  PteContents = *PointerPte;
5277 
5278  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
5279 
5280  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (&PteContents);
5281 
5282  if (!MI_IS_PFN (PageFrameIndex)) {
5283 
5284  CacheAttribute = MiCached;

5286  if ((MI_IS_CACHING_DISABLED (&PteContents)) &&
5287  (PteContents.u.Hard.WriteThrough == 1)) {

5291  else if ((MiWriteCombiningPtes == TRUE) &&
